<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12092l"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12092l">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12092l"> 92(l)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> fiancees stick pins in / S. Gwirek&apos;s nose / (Hindenberg)</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">A Ploumanac&apos;h, sur un rocher au bord de la gr&egrave;ve se trouve l&apos;oratoire de <i>Zant Gwirek</i> (Saint-Guirec). C&apos;est une toute petite construction au milieu de laquelle se trouvait une statue en bois repr&eacute;sentant ce bienheureux. Les jeunes filles d&eacute;sireuses de se marier dans l&apos;ann&eacute;e allaient piquer une &eacute;pingle dans le nez du saint. <br><font color="green">[In Ploumanac&apos;h, on a rock at the beach one can find the oratory of <i>Zant Gwirek </i>(Saint-Guirec). This is a small construction in the middle of which there is a wooden statue of the saint. Young girls who want to marry that year come and stick a pin in the nose of the saint.]</font> <small> Paul-Yves S&eacute;billot, <a name="RDTP" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#RDTP"><cite title="source">Traditions et coutumes de Basse Bretagne</cite></a> (1904) 349</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: During the first world war there were wooden statues of Paul von Hindenburg all over Germany and people would nail money to them for war bonds.</mm> </dd></dl>
